Enterprises and governments are facing the most aggressive threat environment in their
history. What is the main issue that is causing attacks to be more profound or wide-
reaching?
A. Adversaries have become smarter, better organized, and more persistent as they look to
gain information capital and IP.
B. At any point in time, there are 200-300 potential security vulnerabilities representing
thousands of potential ways to be exploited.
C. Very few technology executives can confidently answer the simple question from their
CEO: "How secure is my business?"
D. Cyber threats are proven to be proliferating much slower.
Answer: B

Answer: C
